OL,4,CUniversal basic income to be tested in
OL,5,CWales
OL,6, A universal basic income scheme is to
OL,7, be trialled in Wales, meaning adults,
OL,8, regardless of their means, will receive
OL,9, a regular sum of money.
OL,11,FThe idea is that this would cover the
OL,12,Fbasic cost of living.
OL,14,FFirst Minister Mark Drakeford said the
OL,15,Fpilot would "see whether the promises
OL,16,Fthat basic income holds out are
OL,17,Fgenuinely delivered" in people's lives.
OL,19,FBut the Conservatives said Wales should
OL,20,Fnot become "a petri dish for failed
OL,21,Fleft-wing policies".
